15
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:53,960
[2018]
[Jirisan National Park Interpretation Office]

16
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:59,240
[2018]
[Jirisan National Park Haedong Ranger Station]

17
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,584
Search Team 1, moving to the falling rock zone.

18
00:04:12,585 --> 00:04:15,129
Volunteer Team 1, arriving at the trail entrance.

19
00:04:28,851 --> 00:04:29,851
Are you new?

20
00:04:29,852 --> 00:04:31,270
Yes, Sir. Hello.

21
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,262
- I just got dispatched to the Haedo—
- Jung Goo Yeong!

22
00:04:33,262 --> 00:04:35,625
Yes?

23
00:04:35,625 --> 00:04:37,126
Follow him.

24
00:04:37,126 --> 00:04:37,902
To where…?

25
00:04:37,903 --> 00:04:40,786
The mountain. It's a missing case.

26
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:42,823
Yes, Sir!

27
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:56,671
Why? Are you going to wear those?

28
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,781
Let's go, hurry up!

29
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:27,075
Hurry, get on. Hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry.

30
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:42,591
Ranger station to all rangers.

31
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:44,984
Name of the lost hiker, Yeom Seung Hoon. Age 14.

32
00:05:44,984 --> 00:05:47,471
Time of climb, 11:45 a.m. yesterday.
[Time of accident: 8.23.2018 5:25 p.m.]
[Time of climb 8.23.2018 11:45 a.m.]

33
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,872
He used the Haedong Ranger Station trail.
[Lives without parents, left behind a note "I'm sorry, Grandma," Signs of possible suicide]

34
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:57,230
Top, white shirt. Bottom, grey pants.

35
00:05:57,231 --> 00:06:01,417
Bokseon Middle School uniform with white sneakers. And a sky blue backpack.

36
00:06:01,417 --> 00:06:04,821
The last place he used his cellphone was the Samheungbong Peak communication tower.

37
00:06:04,822 --> 00:06:08,200
It matches the statement of the witness who saw him last.

38
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:13,614
The first search area was 3 km within that communication tower.

39
00:06:17,994 --> 00:06:19,928
Haedong Ranger Station,

40
00:06:23,524 --> 00:06:25,434
Bidam Shelter,

41
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:31,290
and Jangteomok Shelter rangers makes up Search Team 1.

42
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:33,700
[Jangteomok Shelter]

43
00:06:39,890 --> 00:06:41,783
Seseok Shelter,

44
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,786
Wusong Shelter,

45
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:50,125
Moojin Ranger Station rangers searched as Search Team 2,

46
00:06:51,135 --> 00:06:53,513
but failed to track the hiker.

47
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:57,741
We'll expand to 10 km and begin the second search.

48
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:04,665
Civilian Volunteer fire department takes section A, the unrestricted trail.
[Access allowed as per environment protection and parks regulations - System in place to monitor safety]

49
00:07:05,174 --> 00:07:08,577
911's Mountain Rescue Team takes area B.

50
00:07:10,087 --> 00:07:15,034
Restricted Trail sections C and D for park ranger teams 1 and 2,
[Restricted trail to protect the environment and wild animals - Potential danger - limited cell phone coverage]

51
00:07:15,034 --> 00:07:17,253
and the support team.

52
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:21,106
Considering the fact that the hiker had no gear on,

53
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:23,733
the golden time is only 30 hours.

54
00:07:23,734 --> 00:07:29,573
It's been 23 hours and we have 7 hours left. We have to find him within that time.

55
00:08:09,707 --> 00:08:13,617
- How's the climate?
- The typhoon's moving north faster than expected.

56
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:16,169
Falling rocks! Watch out!

57
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:32,769
Step back, it's dangerous.

58
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:18,180
Hey!

59
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:43,758
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

60
00:09:43,758 --> 00:09:46,635
Bring a stretcher, get an ambulance ready.

61
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:53,373
Min Seok. Min Seok!

62
00:09:53,884 --> 00:09:56,019
- Is he all right?
- I think so.

63
00:09:56,019 --> 00:09:57,838
- Are you okay?
- Take all his clothes off.

64
00:09:57,838 --> 00:09:59,590
Yeah, okay.

65
00:09:59,590 --> 00:10:02,852
Search Team 1, a ranger has been injured due to falling rocks...

66
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:05,000
We need to take him to the hospital first. Possible bleeding...

67
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,450
Excuse...

68
00:10:08,015 --> 00:10:10,233
Are you all right?

69
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:14,796
Search Team 1, heading to Yangseok Peak now...

70
00:10:14,796 --> 00:10:17,297
And you are…?

71
00:10:17,297 --> 00:10:21,119
Kang Hyun Jo. I just got posted here.

72
00:10:21,119 --> 00:10:23,472
We sent Min Seok to the hospital.

73
00:10:23,472 --> 00:10:25,732
Take the newbie instead.

74
00:10:26,725 --> 00:10:28,893
Oh, by the way…

75
00:10:28,893 --> 00:10:30,253
Demon Seo is her nickname.

76
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:31,504
Be careful so she doesn't bite you.

77
00:10:31,553 --> 00:10:33,105
Pardon?

78
00:10:34,775 --> 00:10:37,517
Search is done in pairs. You know that, right?

79
00:10:37,517 --> 00:10:39,320
Fix your shoelaces and stay close.

80
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:41,523
If you lag behind, I'll abandon you.

81
00:10:43,075 --> 00:10:44,575
Yes!

82
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:07,124
Volunteer Team 1.

83
00:11:07,124 --> 00:11:08,725
Searching the 7 km area on the trail.

84
00:11:08,725 --> 00:11:10,620
No missing hiker found.
[Soomgol Rock]

85
00:11:10,620 --> 00:11:13,770
[Knife Rock]

86
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:22,545
Rescue Team 1, at Knife Rock, we haven't found the hiker.

87
00:11:23,641 --> 00:11:28,244
Typhoon Bitak is heading north at a much faster speed than anticipated.

88
00:11:28,244 --> 00:11:31,498
It was formed in the sea southeast of Okinawa,

89
00:11:31,498 --> 00:11:35,001
and is heading north at 15 km per hour.

90
00:11:35,001 --> 00:11:40,323
It will pass Jeju and Namhae around 10:00 p.m. tonight.

91
00:11:40,324 --> 00:11:46,705
We're expecting up to 300 ml of rain in the Jeju and Jirisan areas.

92
00:11:46,705 --> 00:11:51,209
Please protect your facilities from the strong wind.

93
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:16,501
Seung Hoon!

94
00:12:55,015 --> 00:12:56,983
He's not here.

95
00:12:58,711 --> 00:13:01,312
Ghost Rock. Yangseokbong Peak. The hiker can't be seen.

96
00:13:01,312 --> 00:13:03,406
We'll move to Seonghwang Tree.

97
00:13:26,797 --> 00:13:29,065
Seung Hoon!

98
00:13:32,411 --> 00:13:33,879
Seung Hoon!

99
00:13:33,879 --> 00:13:36,247
Where's Seonghwang Tree?

100
00:13:36,247 --> 00:13:38,708
It's a place where many people die.

101
00:13:38,708 --> 00:13:41,986
So all the places we've searched so far are suicide points?

102
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:46,174
Yes. Once it happens, it happens again and again at the same places.

103
00:13:46,174 --> 00:13:51,555
Does that mean… we've been looking for a dead kid?

104
00:13:54,642 --> 00:13:56,184
Don't say such an unlucky thing.

105
00:13:56,184 --> 00:13:57,769
Who said we are looking for a dead kid?

106
00:13:57,769 --> 00:14:00,664
We're trying to find him to stop him from dying.

107
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:10,307
Wait for me!

108
00:14:21,235 --> 00:14:23,418
Search Team 1. Weather's getting worse.

109
00:14:23,418 --> 00:14:25,989
We'll join at Doongji Tree and search together.

110
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,381
Search Team 2. At Dosang Falls now.

111
00:14:28,381 --> 00:14:31,060
We'll join the search, too.

112
00:14:31,060 --> 00:14:34,489
Typhoon Bitak is accompanying strong wind of over 50 meters per second in speed.

113
00:14:34,489 --> 00:14:37,809
It will reach the peninsula at around 10:00 p.m. tonight.

114
00:14:37,809 --> 00:14:42,313
There is a storm warning on Jeju and in Jeonnam Province.

115
00:14:42,313 --> 00:14:45,099
Have you not found him yet?

116
00:14:45,099 --> 00:14:49,809
- I'm afraid not.
- We pulled out the dogs and rescuers.

117
00:14:49,809 --> 00:14:52,866
The dogs' sense of scent doesn't work well in the rain.

118
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:56,210
Yes, I understand.

119
00:14:58,706 --> 00:15:01,258
The missing hiker's family is here.

120
00:15:01,258 --> 00:15:02,834
Search Team 4. Search Team 4.

121
00:15:02,834 --> 00:15:06,062
He's the commander in charge of the search.

122
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:14,062
I'm sorry… because of my grandson.

123
00:15:14,062 --> 00:15:17,196
- I'm really sorry.
- Not at all, Ma'am.

124
00:15:17,196 --> 00:15:19,968
You must have traveled far. Please take a rest.

125
00:15:19,968 --> 00:15:24,931
We'll let you know right away if we hear anything.

126
00:15:26,275 --> 00:15:29,678
Gyung Seon, please escort her to the night duty room for rest.

127
00:15:29,678 --> 00:15:32,478
- This way, please.
- Please get some rest.

128
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:50,156
Search Team 4. The weather's turned very bad.

129
00:15:50,156 --> 00:15:52,267
What should we do?

130
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:46,237
Search Team 2, taking a detour. The water level's too high.

131
00:16:46,237 --> 00:16:50,658
Volunteer Team 1, pausing the search and evacuating to a shelter.

132
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:05,700
The current is too strong!

133
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:13,100
Grab him! Get in!

134
00:17:14,383 --> 00:17:18,267
One, two! One, two!

135
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:26,353
Search Team 3, man down!

136
00:17:54,656 --> 00:17:56,107
Yours, too.

137
00:17:56,107 --> 00:17:59,307
- Excuse me?
- We can pick them up later, so throw yours out too.

138
00:18:01,722 --> 00:18:03,840
Why are you doing this?

139
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,884
This is a lightning-prone area.

140
00:18:09,646 --> 00:18:15,635
There must be a good reason we're passing here in this weather.

141
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:17,136
This is the shortcut.

142
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,596
We can save an hour.

143
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:22,075
We must join them for the search before things get worse.

144
00:18:24,119 --> 00:18:26,894
Never go near a big tree, it'll work as a lightning rod.

145
00:18:26,894 --> 00:18:28,998
Grab something else even if you slip.

146
00:18:28,998 --> 00:18:31,083
If there's nothing to grab, just roll down.

147
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:34,002
That'll be faster.

148
00:18:34,002 --> 00:18:36,346
All of this...

149
00:18:43,163 --> 00:18:45,965
Senior! Wait!

150
00:19:22,302 --> 00:19:24,012
Are you okay?

151
00:19:29,351 --> 00:19:31,677
Senior, over there.

152
00:19:31,677 --> 00:19:34,530
Look. Look over there.

153
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:44,464
Search Team 5, Under Bidam Cliff.

154
00:19:44,464 --> 00:19:47,088
We found a backpack that looks like that of the hiker's.

155
00:19:47,088 --> 00:19:48,678
Are you sure?

156
00:19:49,955 --> 00:19:52,298
It's a sky blue backpack.

157
00:19:55,710 --> 00:19:58,630
[Yeom Seung Hoon | Bokseon Middle School, Grade 1, Home Room 5 | 7ª Grade in the USA]

158
00:19:58,630 --> 00:20:00,324
It's his backpack for sure.

159
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:05,870
What about the hiker?

160
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:08,114
Did he fall with his backpack?

161
00:20:08,114 --> 00:20:09,890
No, we don't see the hiker.

162
00:20:09,890 --> 00:20:11,292
No signs of a crash either.

163
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:13,903
It looks like only his backpack fell.

164
00:20:16,481 --> 00:20:18,081
Senior,

165
00:20:18,081 --> 00:20:20,560
isn't this Jirisan?

166
00:20:25,157 --> 00:20:29,349
Sir, there's a photo of a wildflower habitat above Bidam Cliff.

167
00:20:29,349 --> 00:20:31,988
I think that was the hiker's destination.

168
00:20:31,988 --> 00:20:34,432
We must search there.

169
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:48,055
It takes at least three hours to get there, even on sunny days.

170
00:20:48,055 --> 00:20:52,625
It'll take twice as long... on a day like this.

171
00:20:53,643 --> 00:20:57,686
We'll go. Please give us permission to search.

172
00:20:57,686 --> 00:20:59,524
Retreat.

173
00:21:08,408 --> 00:21:10,059
Who is it?

174
00:21:11,912 --> 00:21:13,538
Chief.

175
00:21:13,538 --> 00:21:16,358
The 30-hour golden time is almost up.

176
00:21:16,358 --> 00:21:19,777
The missing hiker's not even wearing proper gear.

177
00:21:19,778 --> 00:21:23,656
If he's alive, we must go now.

178
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:30,454
He might already be dead.

179
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:33,082
He came to the mountain to kill himself.
 [Possible suicide attempt, Bullied at school]

180
00:21:33,082 --> 00:21:36,219
Are you giving up your life for a dead body?

181
00:21:36,219 --> 00:21:40,387
If something happens to you, other rangers must come to help.

182
00:21:40,387 --> 00:21:43,618
Will you take responsibility for their lives?

183
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:53,794
The wind speed's over 20 m/s.

184
00:21:53,794 --> 00:21:55,496
There's no time.

185
00:21:55,496 --> 00:21:57,739
Retreat this second!

186
00:21:57,739 --> 00:22:00,151
This is an order.

187
00:22:08,201 --> 00:22:10,653
Withdraw all teams.

188
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:18,327
Are we really going back?

189
00:22:18,327 --> 00:22:23,290
You said we must look now if he's alive.

190
00:22:23,290 --> 00:22:24,233
Let's go back.

191
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:25,918
Senior.

192
00:23:29,507 --> 00:23:33,026
Hey, newbie! Are you okay?

193
00:23:33,026 --> 00:23:35,454
Demon Seo is indeed ruthless.

194
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:36,890
Our Demon Seo.

195
00:23:36,890 --> 00:23:40,227
How could she drag you to a lightning zone in the storm?

196
00:23:40,227 --> 00:23:42,620
Where's Seung Hoon?

197
00:23:42,620 --> 00:23:45,464
Look after yourself first. Your body comes first.

198
00:23:45,465 --> 00:23:49,936
Dude, how can a ranger say something like that?

199
00:23:49,936 --> 00:23:51,887
To a newbie at that.

200
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:56,800
A ranger must protect the mountain even if his body is torn to pieces, understand?

201
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:03,500
I'll say this as a team leader.

202
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,986
You must be vigilant.

203
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:08,513
I'm so sick of this. Sick of it.

204
00:24:08,513 --> 00:24:10,030
I'm sick of you.

205
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:13,359
Yes, Sir, Team Leader. I get it.

206
00:24:14,778 --> 00:24:17,097
- If you're not alert, you'll get hurt.
- Ouch.

207
00:24:17,097 --> 00:24:20,074
My head hurts and it hurts to sit.

208
00:24:24,660 --> 00:24:30,710
[Missing time: 23 hours]

209
00:24:36,892 --> 00:24:38,476
What the chief said is right.

210
00:24:38,477 --> 00:24:42,271
We'll resume in the morning after the storm's passed.

211
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:44,715
Get some rest until then.

212
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:49,937
What do we tell his family?

213
00:24:49,937 --> 00:24:52,923
We have to tell the truth.

214
00:24:56,661 --> 00:24:58,204
Yes, this is Jirisan National Park.

215
00:24:58,205 --> 00:25:01,266
So, we made a bet among friends.

216
00:25:01,266 --> 00:25:02,833
How high is Cheonwangbong Peak?

217
00:25:02,834 --> 00:25:06,069
It's 1,915 m.

218
00:25:06,069 --> 00:25:09,556
Including the stone monument?

219
00:25:10,717 --> 00:25:12,702
Then it's 1,916.35 m.

220
00:25:12,702 --> 00:25:14,837
I'm hanging up now.

221
00:25:18,058 --> 00:25:19,658
Get some rest.

222
00:25:30,195 --> 00:25:32,112
Shouldn't you get some herbal medicine even if it tastes terrible?

223
00:25:32,113 --> 00:25:35,091
How can a ranger collapse so easily?

224
00:25:35,091 --> 00:25:36,985
He's not dead.

225
00:25:38,286 --> 00:25:40,914
How do you know?

226
00:25:40,914 --> 00:25:43,666
He's alive for sure.

227
00:25:45,085 --> 00:25:48,129
We can't keep searching based on your guess.

228
00:26:17,300 --> 00:26:24,600
[Family Communication Report]
[Impressive Education Filled with Happiness]
[Classroom and Education Information for Parents]

229
00:26:35,570 --> 00:26:42,450
[Lives with grandma without parents]
[Left a final note, "I'm sorry, Grandma."]
[Signs of suicide, a missing report filed]
[Bullied at school...]

230
00:26:50,410 --> 00:26:56,740
[Elementary School Level X]
[Not even Elementary School Level]

231
00:27:57,467 --> 00:27:59,602
Please help me.

232
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:12,390
Senior.

233
00:28:14,442 --> 00:28:17,795
I didn't know what to tell her.

234
00:28:34,963 --> 00:28:37,548
We had to stop the search.

235
00:28:42,971 --> 00:28:46,306
But we'll resume when the storm dies down, so…

236
00:28:46,307 --> 00:28:49,894
I'm sorry… I'm sorry.

237
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:49,480
[Wind Speed: 32.6]
[[Wind direction: SouthWest]
[Precipitation level: 35.0 mm]

238
00:32:07,675 --> 00:32:10,744
Senior! Are you okay?

239
00:32:18,728 --> 00:32:21,453
Are you insane? Did you follow me?

240
00:32:21,453 --> 00:32:23,682
Where do you think this is?

241
00:32:25,943 --> 00:32:30,022
If I'm insane, so are you.

242
00:32:32,450 --> 00:32:35,544
At least I won't be lonely, being in a crazy pair.

243
00:32:42,268 --> 00:32:47,903
I thought… I'd regret it if I didn't come.

244
00:32:47,903 --> 00:32:50,568
Isn't that why you're here, too?

245
00:32:50,568 --> 00:32:53,290
Let's say he really is alive.

246
00:32:53,290 --> 00:32:55,890
He'll die if we don't rescue him now.

247
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:03,915
Seeing as I am here already, please take me with you.

248
00:33:03,915 --> 00:33:06,475
You said a search is done in pairs.

249
00:33:07,527 --> 00:33:11,989
If you whine along the way, I'll kill you.

250
00:33:13,274 --> 00:33:16,744
It's not like you'll notice if I whine.

251
00:33:16,744 --> 00:33:20,014
It's much more dangerous than you can imagine.

252
00:33:20,790 --> 00:33:23,943
Isn't our job always dangerous?

253
00:33:25,878 --> 00:33:31,067
Our job is to come back safely from a dangerous place.

254
00:33:31,067 --> 00:33:32,926
We must be a pillar to each other.

255
00:33:32,927 --> 00:33:35,053
If you get blown away, so do I.

256
00:33:35,054 --> 00:33:37,815
If I fall, so do you.

257
00:33:38,699 --> 00:33:41,168
So let's both be careful.

258
00:33:44,564 --> 00:33:46,148
Copy!

259
00:33:46,650 --> 00:33:53,180
♫ Destiny, it’s all meant to be ♫

260
00:33:53,180 --> 00:34:00,910
♫ I will never let you go, never let you fall ♫

261
00:34:00,910 --> 00:34:06,120
♫ Spend your life? ♫

262
00:34:40,620 --> 00:34:42,504
Hey!

263
00:34:43,873 --> 00:34:46,308
What the hell are you doing, bastards?

264
00:34:53,591 --> 00:34:55,175
Didn't you hear what the chief said?

265
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:57,886
I'm sorry, Sir. I tried my best to stop them…

266
00:34:57,887 --> 00:34:59,471
But the wind's slowing down.

267
00:34:59,472 --> 00:35:01,014
Soon the sun will rise, too.

268
00:35:01,015 --> 00:35:02,265
Please let us go up.

269
00:35:02,266 --> 00:35:06,354
The search will start after the storm passes entirely.

270
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:09,332
Unpack your gear.

271
00:35:09,332 --> 00:35:11,650
Seo Yi Kang is missing.

272
00:35:15,446 --> 00:35:17,706
So is the newbie.

273
00:35:19,133 --> 00:35:20,575
Their gear's gone, too.

274
00:35:20,576 --> 00:35:22,680
Damn fools, honestly.

275
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,700
Excuse me...

276
00:35:26,082 --> 00:35:30,285
She has something to tell you.

277
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:50,481
Seo Yi Kang.

278
00:36:25,933 --> 00:36:27,935
Yi Kang, where are you?

279
00:36:29,036 --> 00:36:31,397
Answer me, Seo Yi Kang!

280
00:36:32,648 --> 00:36:35,192
Search Team 5, Seo Yi Kang.

281
00:36:35,193 --> 00:36:36,902
Where are you?

282
00:36:37,862 --> 00:36:39,438
I'm sorry, but…

283
00:36:39,438 --> 00:36:41,256
Have you arrived there?

284
00:36:42,074 --> 00:36:44,710
The wildflower habitat above Bidam Cliff.

285
00:36:46,287 --> 00:36:48,396
Yes, Sir.

286
00:36:49,373 --> 00:36:51,330
Seung Hoon...

287
00:36:51,330 --> 00:36:54,000
[Message (1/10)]
[I'm sorry for making you worry, Grandma.]
[8/25 4:01 a.m., your grandson.]

288
00:36:54,003 --> 00:36:56,079
...sent a message.

289
00:37:00,509 --> 00:37:03,895
That message we saw wasn't the last one he sent.

290
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:53,261
Do you remember this place?

291
00:37:54,981 --> 00:37:58,658
We've been here with Mom and Dad.

292
00:37:59,527 --> 00:38:02,238
It's so nice being here.

293
00:38:02,238 --> 00:38:05,232
Let's come back together.

294
00:38:07,340 --> 00:38:13,080
[There are flowers you like here.]
[It's time for you to take your medication. Please do not skip taking them.]
[I love you, Grandma.]
[I'm sorry, Grandma.]

295
00:38:14,208 --> 00:38:18,629
I'm sorry for making you worry.

296
00:39:01,839 --> 00:39:05,901
He's... still alive.

297
00:39:07,094 --> 00:39:11,540
He went from a cellular dead zone to a signal zone on his own.

298
00:39:16,062 --> 00:39:18,855
We're calling him repeatedly, but he's not answering.

299
00:39:18,856 --> 00:39:21,274
I think his battery ran out.

300
00:39:22,318 --> 00:39:24,778
The support team's on their way,

301
00:39:24,779 --> 00:39:28,148
but it'll take them three and a half hours minimum.

302
00:39:31,077 --> 00:39:33,954
You're our only hope now.

303
00:39:33,954 --> 00:39:36,198
You guys have to find him.

304
00:39:37,917 --> 00:39:39,209
Let's split up.

305
00:39:39,210 --> 00:39:41,419
Look for the signal zones on GPS.

306
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:42,837
We'll only search those areas.

307
00:39:42,838 --> 00:39:47,342
We'll look for survival points, not suicide points.

308
00:39:47,343 --> 00:39:48,877
Yes!

309
00:39:55,643 --> 00:40:00,480
Reception area on the way from the habitat to Bidam Cliff.

310
00:40:00,481 --> 00:40:01,898
He'll be there. Hurry!

311
00:40:01,899 --> 00:40:03,691
Golden time's up.

312
00:40:03,692 --> 00:40:05,569
Even if he's alive,

313
00:40:06,737 --> 00:40:07,947
he'll be critically ill.

314
00:40:33,889 --> 00:40:38,017
Those that want to live instinctively look for these places.

315
00:40:38,018 --> 00:40:39,811
Between big rocks.

316
00:40:39,812 --> 00:40:41,980
Inside a big stump.

317
00:40:41,981 --> 00:40:45,568
A tunnel of tightly-woven bushes.

318
00:41:13,304 --> 00:41:16,307
Under a big rock carved like a cave.

319
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:20,186
Where you can hide from the rainstorm and keep your body warm.

320
00:41:20,186 --> 00:41:24,581
That kid, came to the mountain to live.

321
00:41:24,581 --> 00:41:27,443
He would surely have found a place like that.

322
00:42:16,258 --> 00:42:18,243
Any progress?

323
00:42:20,220 --> 00:42:22,147
I haven't found him yet.

324
00:42:22,990 --> 00:42:24,165
He's nowhere to be seen.

325
00:42:24,166 --> 00:42:26,834
I've looked in all the places you mentioned.

326
00:42:26,835 --> 00:42:28,703
But he wasn't there.

327
00:42:32,091 --> 00:42:34,425
He's still alive.

328
00:42:34,426 --> 00:42:37,170
He must be here somewhere.

329
00:42:39,765 --> 00:42:41,642
But where?

330
00:42:47,231 --> 00:42:51,402
Those that want to live instinctively look for these places.

331
00:42:51,402 --> 00:42:54,530
Where you can keep warm.

332
00:42:54,530 --> 00:42:57,232
Between big rocks.

333
00:43:04,415 --> 00:43:08,168
Senior, where are you?

334
00:43:08,168 --> 00:43:09,460
What is it?

335
00:43:09,461 --> 00:43:12,964
Have you seen a weird mark made with twigs and rocks?

336
00:43:12,965 --> 00:43:13,881
No.

337
00:43:13,882 --> 00:43:17,111
Something shaped square. Have you seen it?

338
00:43:17,111 --> 00:43:18,595
I've never seen anything like that.

339
00:43:18,596 --> 00:43:21,154
Why do you ask? Just look for the hiker.

340
00:43:21,154 --> 00:43:23,350
What about a black rock then?

341
00:43:24,268 --> 00:43:25,518
What the heck?

342
00:43:25,519 --> 00:43:27,353
There must be an oak tree nearby.

343
00:43:27,354 --> 00:43:31,125
There were oak tree leaves scattered around.

344
00:43:31,125 --> 00:43:32,809
What on earth…?

345
00:43:35,087 --> 00:43:38,298
Do you mean Sangsuri Rock?

346
00:43:38,298 --> 00:43:41,024
Is there such a place? Is it near here?

347
00:43:41,619 --> 00:43:44,730
But that's outside the reception area.

348
00:43:44,730 --> 00:43:46,289
He's there.

349
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:48,334
He's probably there.

350
00:43:48,334 --> 00:43:49,542
Don't you get it?

351
00:43:49,543 --> 00:43:53,547
If he's there, he couldn't have sent the text.

352
00:43:53,547 --> 00:43:55,965
But we've looked everywhere else.

353
00:43:55,966 --> 00:43:57,718
So, please,

354
00:43:57,718 --> 00:44:01,396
let's make it our final place to look.

355
00:44:59,446 --> 00:45:02,096
Senior, over here!

356
00:45:02,096 --> 00:45:03,517
Senior!

357
00:45:16,296 --> 00:45:17,422
We found him!

358
00:45:17,423 --> 00:45:20,475
The hiker found under Sangsuri Rock at Bidam Cliff!

359
00:45:22,970 --> 00:45:25,163
His state of health?

360
00:45:27,724 --> 00:45:28,933
Seo Yi Kang!

361
00:45:28,934 --> 00:45:30,476
He's unconscious.

362
00:45:30,477 --> 00:45:32,829
His body feels very cold.

363
00:45:33,856 --> 00:45:34,897
His pulse and breathing?

364
00:45:34,898 --> 00:45:36,733
Seung Hoon! Yeom Seung Hoon!

365
00:45:38,652 --> 00:45:41,702
Seung Hoon, open your eyes! Wake-up.

366
00:46:50,807 --> 00:46:53,060
Hey! Stop right there!

367
00:47:00,943 --> 00:47:03,002
You all right?

368
00:47:10,327 --> 00:47:12,078
I'll just carry him on my back.

369
00:47:12,079 --> 00:47:13,813
Put him on my back.

370
00:47:19,795 --> 00:47:20,546
Be careful.

371
00:47:20,547 --> 00:47:21,837
Come down carefully.

372
00:47:21,838 --> 00:47:24,147
Take your time!

373
00:47:46,822 --> 00:47:48,240
Are you okay?

374
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:10,460
- Over here!
- There they are.

375
00:48:18,520 --> 00:48:20,655
Check his vitals.

376
00:48:24,443 --> 00:48:26,870
Pulse and breathing, normal.

377
00:48:28,655 --> 00:48:29,614
Great!

378
00:48:29,615 --> 00:48:31,949
Take the lady with you to the hospital.

379
00:48:31,950 --> 00:48:33,693
Yes, Sir.

380
00:48:35,746 --> 00:48:37,664
Take care of her.

381
00:48:39,166 --> 00:48:41,242
See you in a bit.

382
00:48:46,340 --> 00:48:47,548
We're at the bottom.

383
00:48:47,549 --> 00:48:49,800
His pulse is normal, on the way to the hospital.

384
00:48:49,801 --> 00:48:52,153
Come down safely.

385
00:49:18,080 --> 00:49:19,455
Great work.

386
00:49:19,456 --> 00:49:21,332
Thank you.

387
00:49:21,333 --> 00:49:22,583
Where is Yi Kang?

388
00:49:22,584 --> 00:49:25,011
She's probably passed out.

389
00:49:31,843 --> 00:49:34,888
Well done, Yi Kang.

390
00:49:36,515 --> 00:49:38,392
Why aren't you responding?

391
00:49:38,392 --> 00:49:40,718
Hey, Yi Kang! Can you hear me?

392
00:49:42,662 --> 00:49:44,106
Hey, Yi Kang!

393
00:49:44,815 --> 00:49:46,830
Did she just turn it off?

394
00:49:46,830 --> 00:49:52,910
♫ Our memories hold on to times of the past ♫

395
00:49:52,910 --> 00:50:00,000
♫ Something's gonna bring it to the air tonight.
Can't imagine my life without you ♫

396
00:50:00,260 --> 00:50:03,590
♫ Something's gonna bring it to the air tonight.
Can't imagine my life without you ♫

397
00:50:03,590 --> 00:50:10,910
♫ And when the world needs something, about to feel this way ♫

398
00:50:13,420 --> 00:50:19,240
♫ When we were young, everything we did ♫

399
00:50:19,240 --> 00:50:25,120
♫ When we were young, and wild and free ♫

400
00:50:25,120 --> 00:50:31,530
♫ Tell me the truth, walk across to life ♫

401
00:50:31,530 --> 00:50:36,190
♫ There's going to be everything I need ♫

402
00:50:36,190 --> 00:50:38,117
Will you not spring yourself up here?

403
00:50:38,118 --> 00:50:41,286
Aren't you going to train?

404
00:50:41,286 --> 00:50:45,174
In… just a sec… Let's rest a bit.

405
00:50:45,174 --> 00:50:46,518
Are you here to play?

406
00:50:46,518 --> 00:50:49,971
How can you save anyone at that pace?

407
00:50:49,971 --> 00:50:52,548
If there is one thing that Jirisan is, is that it's big.

408
00:50:52,549 --> 00:50:56,194
Stranded hikers will be dead while you rest like that.

409
00:50:56,194 --> 00:50:57,779
I think… I'm really dying.

410
00:50:57,779 --> 00:51:01,174
You got your patrol area assigned, right?

411
00:51:01,174 --> 00:51:03,076
Have you been there?

412
00:51:03,076 --> 00:51:04,477
No, not yet…

413
00:51:04,478 --> 00:51:07,313
Our main task is to guard this mountain.

414
00:51:07,314 --> 00:51:13,010
You must have all the place names, tree species, and distribution of vegetation memorized by heart.

415
00:51:13,010 --> 00:51:15,154
Demon Seo…

416
00:51:15,155 --> 00:51:17,639
Do you have a death wish?

417
00:51:17,639 --> 00:51:20,059
No, Senior.

418
00:51:20,059 --> 00:51:23,180
Even if I die…

419
00:51:25,313 --> 00:51:27,617
Can I have a sip of water?

420
00:51:32,839 --> 00:51:36,401
Yes. At Sohn Rock.

421
00:51:38,720 --> 00:51:41,314
Okay. Coming.

422
00:51:42,682 --> 00:51:44,141
Is this Sohn Rock?

423
00:51:44,142 --> 00:51:46,394
Sohn, as in hand?

424
00:52:00,942 --> 00:52:03,244
They're making it harder to go down.

425
00:52:03,245 --> 00:52:06,580
Why would they have a date at such a tough place, not a pub?

426
00:52:06,581 --> 00:52:09,142
That's so annoying.

427
00:52:09,876 --> 00:52:13,563
Should I… hold your hand?

428
00:52:17,509 --> 00:52:20,319
Shut up and follow me.

429
00:52:20,319 --> 00:52:22,960
Wait… Slow down…

430
00:52:36,611 --> 00:52:38,487
How did you find this place?

431
00:52:38,488 --> 00:52:40,398
It wasn't me.

432
00:52:40,398 --> 00:52:42,200
He did.

433
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,158
Newbie.

434
00:52:43,159 --> 00:52:44,859
Yes?

435
00:52:44,859 --> 00:52:46,454
How did you know about this place?

436
00:52:46,454 --> 00:52:48,814
Well, umm…

437
00:52:51,293 --> 00:52:54,445
Let's say… the mountain told me.

438
00:52:54,445 --> 00:52:56,772
The mountain?

439
00:52:56,772 --> 00:52:59,049
That's believable.

440
00:52:59,049 --> 00:53:03,220
People have been serving Jirisan from before the Three Kingdoms.
(Refers to the three kingdoms of Goguryeo, Baekje, and Silla)

441
00:53:03,221 --> 00:53:05,723
Being an object of faith for such a long time,

442
00:53:05,724 --> 00:53:08,017
can't just be a superstition.

443
00:53:08,018 --> 00:53:12,413
There's energy in this mountain that's difficult to explain.

444
00:53:12,413 --> 00:53:14,957
That's what I mean.

445
00:53:14,957 --> 00:53:16,150
This time, for instance,

446
00:53:16,151 --> 00:53:20,362
there's no reception here, but a text message was sent.

447
00:53:20,363 --> 00:53:24,158
- The mountain saved the kid.
- Ah.

448
00:53:26,411 --> 00:53:28,579
Stop the nonsense.

449
00:53:28,580 --> 00:53:30,831
So what? What is it, anyway?

450
00:53:30,832 --> 00:53:32,817
Oh, that.

451
00:53:32,817 --> 00:53:34,692
This is...

452
00:53:34,692 --> 00:53:37,397
how the red commies communicated with each other.

453
00:53:37,397 --> 00:53:40,090
When they fell behind from their team or was out of contact,

454
00:53:40,091 --> 00:53:43,586
they made a secret code like this to communicate.

455
00:53:44,154 --> 00:53:46,447
That's still there?

456
00:53:46,447 --> 00:53:49,433
They pick a spot that no one else will discover.

457
00:53:49,434 --> 00:53:50,827
A place that won't be…

458
00:53:50,827 --> 00:53:52,561
destroyed in the wind and rain.

459
00:53:52,562 --> 00:53:53,646
Like this place.

460
00:53:53,647 --> 00:53:56,107
What do those twigs signify?

461
00:53:56,107 --> 00:53:57,650
It was to notify their location,

462
00:53:57,651 --> 00:54:00,002
or so we assume.

463
00:54:00,879 --> 00:54:03,722
I must go somewhere now.

464
00:54:05,784 --> 00:54:07,620
Thank you for calling me.

465
00:54:07,620 --> 00:54:09,390
See you later.

466
00:54:11,760 --> 00:54:13,290
Wait a moment.

467
00:54:14,726 --> 00:54:15,668
Here.

468
00:54:15,669 --> 00:54:18,128
I'm Kim Sol, a cultural resources foundation researcher.

469
00:54:18,129 --> 00:54:23,401
If you happen to find another historical place like this, please call me!

470
00:54:23,401 --> 00:54:24,886
All right.

471
00:54:33,478 --> 00:54:36,873
This must be quite valuable.

472
00:54:37,999 --> 00:54:39,959
This here,

473
00:54:39,959 --> 00:54:46,515
could be useful when we can't use radio or cellphones on the restricted trails.

474
00:54:46,515 --> 00:54:49,618
It's perfect for signaling a lost hiker's location.

475
00:54:49,619 --> 00:54:52,138
Look here, Senior.

476
00:54:54,332 --> 00:54:58,352
Pretend these rocks are Bidam Cliff.

477
00:54:58,352 --> 00:55:00,338
Here…

478
00:55:01,881 --> 00:55:04,717
Stick a twig in it.

479
00:55:08,096 --> 00:55:12,125
See? It's right where Sangsuri Rock is.

480
00:55:15,645 --> 00:55:17,479
Now tell me the truth.

481
00:55:17,480 --> 00:55:19,782
How did you find this place?

482
00:55:29,743 --> 00:55:33,170
I saw this place.

483
00:55:36,958 --> 00:55:38,960
It's not my first time.

484
00:55:38,960 --> 00:55:41,111
I keep seeing…

485
00:55:41,111 --> 00:55:44,515
where missing hikers are on this mountain.

486
00:55:49,429 --> 00:55:51,664
You really are crazy.

487
00:56:05,028 --> 00:56:06,496
Are we really going on patrol?

488
00:56:06,496 --> 00:56:08,372
Wait for me!

489
00:56:10,558 --> 00:56:12,426
I'm coming!

490
00:56:46,860 --> 00:56:51,960
[2020]

491
00:57:00,680 --> 00:57:04,050
[Report on the Search and Rescue of Missing Persons]

492
00:57:09,592 --> 00:57:13,846
The official search report of the Yiseokjae incident is over as of today.

493
00:57:13,847 --> 00:57:16,390
Return to your ranger station or shelter,

494
00:57:16,391 --> 00:57:19,543
and focus on your tasks.

495
00:57:20,328 --> 00:57:21,871
Then…

496
00:57:22,856 --> 00:57:26,775
If we end like this, what about the lost hiker?

497
00:57:33,575 --> 00:57:36,702
If that many people searched for over a month and couldn't find him,

498
00:57:36,703 --> 00:57:38,988
it's hopeless.

499
00:57:42,167 --> 00:57:45,419
The autumn leaves season starts next week.

500
00:57:45,420 --> 00:57:47,212
There will be a lot more tourists.

501
00:57:47,213 --> 00:57:50,132
Check the safety facilities and do a good base duty.

502
00:57:50,133 --> 00:57:52,017
Yes, Sir.

503
00:57:52,017 --> 00:57:55,637
But when are we getting a new member?

504
00:57:55,638 --> 00:57:58,148
We've had a vacancy for a while.

505
00:58:03,146 --> 00:58:04,313
Someone's coming.

506
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:07,164
Really? Who?

507
00:58:07,164 --> 00:58:11,153
I hope it's someone experienced, not a newbie like her.

508
00:58:13,031 --> 00:58:14,966
It's someone you know.

509
00:58:14,966 --> 00:58:16,642
Who is it?

510
00:58:37,305 --> 00:58:38,680
Seo Yi Kang?

511
00:58:38,681 --> 00:58:40,374
Yes.

512
00:58:42,143 --> 00:58:45,145
The Seo Yi Kang that I know?

513
00:58:47,123 --> 00:58:48,523
Yes.

514
00:58:50,268 --> 00:58:52,010
No way.

515
00:58:52,010 --> 00:58:55,139
She hasn't quit yet?

516
00:58:55,139 --> 00:58:57,791
She asked to be reinstated.

517
00:58:58,743 --> 00:59:00,736
Even so, not her.

518
00:59:03,748 --> 00:59:06,800
Who is she? Why is this a big deal?

519
00:59:54,674 --> 00:59:57,001
Long time no see.

520
00:59:58,152 --> 00:59:59,978
Yes, it's been a long while.

521
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:04,391
How have you been?

522
01:00:05,993 --> 01:00:07,353
You…

523
01:00:08,813 --> 01:00:10,813
Why are you back?

524
01:00:14,694 --> 01:00:16,528
What do you mean by "why"?

525
01:00:16,529 --> 01:00:20,449
She's Ranger Seo Yi Kang, who knows this mountain best.

526
01:00:20,449 --> 01:00:23,667
- You know what I mean.
- Shouldn't you be on patrol?

527
01:00:31,794 --> 01:00:33,362
Grab your gear and follow me.

528
01:00:33,362 --> 01:00:34,763
Okay…

529
01:00:58,300 --> 01:01:01,400
[Report on the Search of Missing Persons at the Jirisan National Park]

530
01:01:04,000 --> 01:01:06,070
Coffee.

531
01:01:06,070 --> 01:01:07,997
Is it a missing case?

532
01:01:08,873 --> 01:01:10,474
Yes.

533
01:01:10,474 --> 01:01:13,168
Yiseokjae, that's near Yiseok Falls, right?

534
01:01:13,169 --> 01:01:16,096
Where did this person go missing?

535
01:01:16,096 --> 01:01:18,907
There's no witness.

536
01:01:22,887 --> 01:01:25,139
Why are you back?

537
01:01:32,855 --> 01:01:37,551
Have you looked near Gaeam Falls?

538
01:01:37,551 --> 01:01:40,195
That's in the opposite direction to Yiseok valley.

539
01:01:40,196 --> 01:01:42,397
You know that well.

540
01:01:44,367 --> 01:01:47,144
I think we should search there.

541
01:01:53,100 --> 01:01:55,752
Did you get a tip-off?

542
01:01:55,752 --> 01:01:57,888
Please.

543
01:02:02,360 --> 01:02:04,060
Pass me the card.

544
01:02:11,744 --> 01:02:13,495
Just a sec.

545
01:02:20,461 --> 01:02:21,879
Senior.

546
01:02:21,879 --> 01:02:23,196
Well…

547
01:02:23,197 --> 01:02:26,433
What happened to that senior?

548
01:02:26,433 --> 01:02:29,253
What do you think happened on a mountain?

549
01:02:29,253 --> 01:02:32,013
They were stranded.

550
01:02:32,013 --> 01:02:33,949
Stranded?

551
01:02:35,251 --> 01:02:39,363
Why did they have to go up there in heavy snow?

552
01:02:39,363 --> 01:02:43,467
We almost died rescuing them.

553
01:02:43,467 --> 01:02:44,927
But.

554
01:02:44,927 --> 01:02:46,845
Did you say "them"?

555
01:02:46,845 --> 01:02:48,430
You mean…

556
01:02:48,430 --> 01:02:51,241
Someone else went missing, too?

557
01:02:51,241 --> 01:02:52,984
Why?

558
01:02:55,104 --> 01:02:57,347
Control room speaking.

559
01:02:58,608 --> 01:03:00,901
Yes, Sir.

560
01:03:05,089 --> 01:03:07,758
I don't understand.

561
01:03:07,758 --> 01:03:09,919
I really don't.

562
01:03:09,919 --> 01:03:11,119
Why did he want us to come here?

563
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:12,496
Be careful, it's slippery.

564
01:03:12,497 --> 01:03:14,197
Okay.

565
01:03:21,130 --> 01:03:22,506
What is this place?

566
01:03:22,507 --> 01:03:24,090
Gaeam Falls.

567
01:03:24,091 --> 01:03:27,477
It's famous for its scenery even though it's in a restricted area.

568
01:03:33,768 --> 01:03:37,980
There's not even a single ant here, what does he want to find here?

569
01:03:42,985 --> 01:03:45,085
Senior.

570
01:03:45,085 --> 01:03:47,013
What's that?

571
01:03:49,283 --> 01:03:51,568
Illegal hikers.

572
01:03:52,845 --> 01:03:57,083
We tell them not to come, but they still do.

573
01:03:58,918 --> 01:04:02,471
They keep trashing the place, that's why we won't let them in here.

574
01:04:10,888 --> 01:04:12,688
Why?

575
01:04:36,620 --> 01:04:41,600
[Yang Geun Tak]

576
01:04:41,600 --> 01:04:44,220
[Hiker: Yang Geun Tak]

577
01:04:47,540 --> 01:04:49,418
It's him.

578
01:04:52,680 --> 01:04:57,248
The missing hiker… we've been looking for.

579
01:05:46,567 --> 01:05:49,177
How did you know?

580
01:05:49,177 --> 01:05:51,596
Hundreds of people looked for over a month in vain.

581
01:05:51,596 --> 01:05:53,682
But you…

582
01:05:54,859 --> 01:05:58,878
You just got here. So how did you know?

583
01:05:58,878 --> 01:06:01,206
I want to know, too.

584
01:06:01,206 --> 01:06:04,092
How did you know…

585
01:06:04,092 --> 01:06:06,136
the missing hiker was there?

586
01:06:11,690 --> 01:06:14,430
[Always being with the mountain]

587
01:06:14,430 --> 01:06:18,761
This is the Jirisan volunteer fire department website.

588
01:06:18,761 --> 01:06:20,951
Did you figure it out from this?

589
01:06:24,330 --> 01:06:26,314
This is a picture of a joint search with the rangers

590
01:06:26,315 --> 01:06:29,025
during this Yiseokjae accident.

591
01:06:29,026 --> 01:06:30,711
And?

592
01:06:39,553 --> 01:06:42,989
Isn't that the mark you discovered

593
01:06:42,989 --> 01:06:45,291
at Sangsuri Rock?

594
01:06:47,670 --> 01:06:50,196
This one's different.

595
01:06:50,196 --> 01:06:53,166
Only Hyun Jo and I knew this signal.

596
01:06:55,636 --> 01:06:58,372
We decided to use this

597
01:06:58,372 --> 01:07:02,851
to signal where a lost hiker is when there's no reception.

598
01:07:02,851 --> 01:07:05,061
So this signal...

599
01:07:05,061 --> 01:07:08,390
pointed to Gaeam Falls?

600
01:07:10,390 --> 01:07:11,860
[Moojin area missing person search in progress]

601
01:07:11,860 --> 01:07:14,195
This was three months ago during the Moojin area accident.

602
01:07:14,196 --> 01:07:16,489
I also found the mark there in the photo.

603
01:07:16,490 --> 01:07:18,616
It was pointing to Seonghwang Tree.

604
01:07:18,617 --> 01:07:22,145
You found the missing person's body there, right?

605
01:07:22,763 --> 01:07:24,363
Yes.

606
01:07:25,933 --> 01:07:29,553
This was six months ago during the Jeonmukgol accident.

607
01:07:30,171 --> 01:07:33,323
And this one was the Oerae Valley accident.

608
01:07:34,216 --> 01:07:36,343
Here too…

609
01:07:36,343 --> 01:07:39,145
It pointed exactly to a missing hiker.

610
01:07:39,145 --> 01:07:40,305
That's impossible.

611
01:07:40,306 --> 01:07:42,699
Maybe it was a prank?

612
01:07:45,478 --> 01:07:49,865
It was exactly at the place Hyun Jo and I decided on.

613
01:07:53,669 --> 01:07:56,421
Someone is sending me a signal.

614
01:07:58,600 --> 01:08:03,620
If it's between you and that Hyun Jo guy…

615
01:08:03,621 --> 01:08:06,181
It must be him.

616
01:08:06,832 --> 01:08:08,542
No.

617
01:08:09,376 --> 01:08:11,411
Hyun Jo…

618
01:08:12,129 --> 01:08:14,748
can't come to this mountain anymore.

619
01:09:08,880 --> 01:09:15,010
[Kang Hyun Jo]
[Saegum Central Hospital]

620
01:09:54,873 --> 01:09:56,975
Someone…

621
01:09:56,975 --> 01:09:59,894
is sending me a signal…

622
01:09:59,894 --> 01:10:02,405
from up there in the mountain.

623
01:10:53,248 --> 01:10:56,026
I wanted to know who that person is.

624
01:11:00,798 --> 01:11:03,024
That's why I returned.

625
01:11:03,650 --> 01:11:09,770
♫ Bleed it out ’til someone’s sacrifice ♫

626
01:11:09,770 --> 01:11:15,400
♫ Like faith without a fear ♫

627
01:11:16,950 --> 01:11:20,410
♫ Feel like I’m grounded ♫

628
01:11:20,410 --> 01:11:23,620
♫ Last thing I wanted ♫

629
01:11:23,620 --> 01:11:28,860
♫ Hold me like you used to do ♫

630
01:11:30,310 --> 01:11:36,950
♫ Be brave, time to face ♫

631
01:11:36,950 --> 01:11:43,750
♫ Last thing I want is to stop and stare ♫

632
01:11:44,470 --> 01:11:47,800
♫ Destiny, it’s all meant to be ♫

633
01:11:47,800 --> 01:11:50,900
[Jirisan]
~ Preview ~

634
01:11:50,900 --> 01:11:54,442
So why did you go there that day?

635
01:11:54,442 --> 01:11:56,102
I'm here because there's something I need to find.

636
01:11:56,102 --> 01:11:58,932
- What is it?
- A dead body.

637
01:11:58,932 --> 01:12:02,525
- Go to the headquarters.
- I'll let you know first if I find anything.

638
01:12:02,526 --> 01:12:05,103
I saw the mark...

639
01:12:05,103 --> 01:12:07,522
But this was the only way.

640
01:12:07,522 --> 01:12:09,999
Who is this person?

641
01:12:09,999 --> 01:12:12,953
Why are you asking about the ribbons?

642
01:12:12,953 --> 01:12:14,328
Moojin Valley, pine tree habitat!

643
01:12:14,329 --> 01:12:18,890
Park ranger down! It's Kang Hyun Jo.
